1
00:00:48,700 --> 00:00:51,800
Do you regret now
that you kissed me?

2
00:00:53,533 --> 00:00:55,333
Tiffany, of course not.

3
00:00:58,100 --> 00:00:59,900
I don't want you to think
that I'm taking advantage

4
00:00:59,967 --> 00:01:01,633
of our friendship.

5
00:01:01,700 --> 00:01:03,367
It's not all your fault.

6
00:01:06,233 --> 00:01:09,333
I also allowed that to happen.

7
00:01:09,433 --> 00:01:12,367
Basti, let's not talk
about this again.

8
00:01:12,433 --> 00:01:15,333
Mikoy, good thing you're here.

9
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:18,900
Where have you been?

10
00:01:18,967 --> 00:01:20,433
Who was with you?

11
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:22,967
I just went to Ms. Vangie.

12
00:01:23,033 --> 00:01:24,400
I just gave her some reminders.

13
00:01:24,467 --> 00:01:26,000
I'm the one who was left behind
and I'm wrong.

14
00:01:26,067 --> 00:01:30,133
I'm the bad one and I'm the one
who forgot.

15
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:31,267
It's always me.

16
00:01:31,333 --> 00:01:33,300
And you are the victim?

17
00:01:33,367 --> 00:01:34,800
Not me, Mikoy.

18
00:01:36,867 --> 00:01:38,800
It was you who left us.

19
00:01:38,867 --> 00:01:41,967
Did you hear what Celeste said?

20
00:01:42,067 --> 00:01:43,933
Yes, last night.

21
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:45,767
I thought he was talking
to Mikoy

22
00:01:45,833 --> 00:01:48,433
because what she referring
to him.

23
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:51,033
Could it be that the two
are starting to like each other

24
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:52,167
again?

25
00:01:52,233 --> 00:01:53,700
Good morning.

26
00:01:53,767 --> 00:01:55,133
I should go.

27
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:56,867
No. You should have your
breakfast first.

28
00:01:56,933 --> 00:01:58,067
I cooked eggs benedict.

29
00:01:58,133 --> 00:01:59,633
Isn't that your favorite?

30
00:01:59,700 --> 00:02:00,933
I got excited because
this is the first time

31
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:01,967
I cooked it again.

32
00:02:02,033 --> 00:02:03,900
You shouldn't have gone out
of your way.

33
00:02:03,967 --> 00:02:06,767
And I shouldn't have slept here.

34
00:02:06,833 --> 00:02:08,233
Come on, Tonito.

35
00:02:08,300 --> 00:02:10,167
I know what you're thinking.

36
00:02:10,233 --> 00:02:13,200
I slept in the other room, okay?

37
00:02:13,267 --> 00:02:16,633
You fell asleep that's why
I didn't wake you up.

38
00:02:16,733 --> 00:02:18,533
And I know you're tired
from work.

39
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:20,900
So come on. Let's just have
breakfast, okay?

40
00:02:20,967 --> 00:02:23,833
About what happened with
Hazel the other day,

41
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:27,533
I'm sorry if our fight
got out of hand.

42
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:29,267
It shouldn't end that way.

43
00:02:29,333 --> 00:02:32,167
Don't worry about me
and your Auntie Adora.

44
00:02:32,233 --> 00:02:34,400
We understand.

45
00:02:34,467 --> 00:02:36,300
Maybe I should also
apologize to Hazel.

46
00:02:36,367 --> 00:02:40,467
I don't want her to harbor
hate towards me.

47
00:02:40,533 --> 00:02:44,333
You know trust is very important
in a relationship.

48
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:46,533
When you start to doubt

49
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:49,200
that's the rust that will
destroy your relationship.

50
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:51,267
I have my doubts about Celeste.

51
00:02:51,333 --> 00:02:53,967
Hazel, someone wants
to talk to you.

52
00:03:06,633 --> 00:03:09,067
Grandmother, come on.

53
00:03:09,133 --> 00:03:09,867
Why?

54
00:03:11,667 --> 00:03:15,133
You'll get something
in the room, right?

55
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,333
Nothing.

56
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:17,400
There is.

57
00:03:17,467 --> 00:03:18,733
What?

58
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:21,467
Grandmother, they will talk.

59
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:26,467
Oh yes, they will talk.

60
00:03:26,533 --> 00:03:29,700
I'll leave you guys.
I have to go.

61
00:03:29,767 --> 00:03:31,467
I'll get something in the room.

62
00:03:31,533 --> 00:03:32,867
Come on.

63
00:03:40,667 --> 00:03:44,067
You probably won't fight
with me here, Celeste.

64
00:03:44,133 --> 00:03:46,400
I didn't fight with you.

65
00:03:46,467 --> 00:03:48,167
You fought with me
and I was annoyed.

66
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:54,400
Anyway, I didn't
come here for that.

67
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:58,600
I came here because I want
to apologize to you.

68
00:03:58,667 --> 00:04:03,433
Sorry if I acted a villain
to all your ideas the other day.

69
00:04:05,933 --> 00:04:07,933
Apology accepted.

70
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,467
I just hope that won't happen
to us again.

71
00:04:13,967 --> 00:04:16,267
Well, everybody deserves
a second chance.

72
00:04:16,333 --> 00:04:21,167
And so, please send me again
the feasibility studies

73
00:04:21,233 --> 00:04:23,667
so I can study them again.

74
00:04:27,033 --> 00:04:28,200
This is for you.

75
00:04:34,333 --> 00:04:35,233
Thank you.

76
00:04:37,133 --> 00:04:38,267
Sounds good...

77
00:04:39,700 --> 00:04:41,133
and I hope this time around

78
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:43,100
I can live up to your high
standards.

79
00:04:44,833 --> 00:04:48,433
Hope this time around
you won't fail.

80
00:04:50,567 --> 00:04:54,267
Anyway, Mikoy and I talked
last night

81
00:04:54,333 --> 00:04:56,233
and I realized that
I don't want trouble.

82
00:04:56,300 --> 00:04:59,133
I don't want negative
energy around anyone.

83
00:05:00,867 --> 00:05:03,567
You and Mikoy talked last night?

84
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:35,300
He didn't tell you?

85
00:05:38,967 --> 00:05:40,867
Where have you been?

86
00:05:40,933 --> 00:05:44,100
Who was with you?

87
00:05:44,167 --> 00:05:46,300
I just went to Ms. Vangie.

88
00:05:46,367 --> 00:05:48,000
I gave her some reminders.

89
00:05:49,567 --> 00:05:50,600
Let's go upstairs.

90
00:05:53,033 --> 00:05:59,367
Anyway, enjoy the pili nuts
and I'll see you soon.

91
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:10,667
Mikoy is really a liar.

92
00:06:34,333 --> 00:06:35,567
Tonito,

93
00:06:37,767 --> 00:06:39,567
do you mind?

94
00:06:39,633 --> 00:06:42,100
Just let me because
this is the last.

95
00:06:46,767 --> 00:06:48,233
Thank you, Aurelia.

96
00:07:07,533 --> 00:07:08,700
Are you okay?

97
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:12,033
Of course.

98
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:15,400
It's just I used to do
this all the time.

99
00:07:17,067 --> 00:07:20,000
I'm sure Celeste will
also do this for you.

100
00:07:24,067 --> 00:07:25,267
Thank you, Aurelia.

101
00:07:25,333 --> 00:07:29,867
I enjoyed your company
especially the eggs benedict.

102
00:07:29,933 --> 00:07:31,467
You haven't changed.

103
00:07:31,533 --> 00:07:34,100
You still know what I like.

104
00:07:34,167 --> 00:07:35,333
Don't worry.

105
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:38,767
I'll teach that to Celeste.

106
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:41,300
I wish you happiness.

107
00:08:02,533 --> 00:08:04,333
Can we still be friends?

108
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:06,900
Of course, good friends.

109
00:08:08,933 --> 00:08:12,767
It's not yet too late for us
to be friends, right?

110
00:08:14,067 --> 00:08:18,000
And I'm sure Tiffany
will be happy

111
00:08:18,067 --> 00:08:20,133
if she finds out about this.

112
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:22,033
Of course.

113
00:08:22,133 --> 00:08:25,467
Even if our family
didn't become whole

114
00:08:25,533 --> 00:08:28,900
at least we're on good terms.

115
00:08:36,667 --> 00:08:40,567
Well, I should get going.

116
00:08:40,633 --> 00:08:41,900
Thank you.

117
00:10:01,967 --> 00:10:03,167
Mr. Ben!

118
00:10:04,467 --> 00:10:05,900
I have good news.

119
00:10:20,733 --> 00:10:22,700
Yes! It's approved!

120
00:10:22,767 --> 00:10:23,733
- It's approved?
- Approved!

121
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:24,933
- It's approved?
- Yes.

122
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:27,067
Our Council of Elders agreed.

123
00:10:27,133 --> 00:10:29,933
Oh my God!

124
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:32,800
They know, once both of you
get married,

125
00:10:32,867 --> 00:10:35,933
your girlfriend Tiffany
will be a resident here.

126
00:10:36,033 --> 00:10:38,700
So you should never break up.

127
00:10:38,767 --> 00:10:40,333
No, Mr. Ben.

128
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:42,567
Tiffany and I will not break up.

129
00:10:42,633 --> 00:10:44,100
Right, sugar pie?

130
00:10:47,233 --> 00:10:49,233
Yes, of course, pumpkin pie.

131
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:14,333
I'm happy that you and Hazel
are okay now.

132
00:11:17,867 --> 00:11:20,000
I don't want any more trouble,
Mikoy.

133
00:11:20,067 --> 00:11:22,667
It's hard if you have
resentment inside.

134
00:11:22,733 --> 00:11:24,200
It's a burden.

135
00:11:24,267 --> 00:11:29,800
So as much as possible I want
negative vibes to disappear.

136
00:11:31,867 --> 00:11:34,700
Sorry too for what I've said.

137
00:11:34,767 --> 00:11:36,567
I'll say it again,
I'm not blaming you.

138
00:11:39,300 --> 00:11:41,233
We have a saying...

139
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:44,533
that some people metbut were not
destined, right?

140
00:11:44,633 --> 00:11:49,567
I mean we can always argue
but nothing will happen.

141
00:11:49,633 --> 00:11:50,733
I'm fine.

142
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:56,167
Just like what you said
we have our own lives now.

143
00:11:56,233 --> 00:12:00,067
So, I hope we will all be happy.

144
00:12:01,833 --> 00:12:02,833
Yeah.

145
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:06,567
Let's be happy with those
with us right now.

146
00:12:08,733 --> 00:12:09,667
Yeah.

147
00:12:09,733 --> 00:12:12,233
Anyway, I'll go ahead.

148
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:14,067
I'll take you home.

149
00:12:14,133 --> 00:12:15,933
No, thank you.

150
00:12:16,033 --> 00:12:17,967
Father is in the next street.

151
00:12:18,033 --> 00:12:20,133
He's waiting for me.

152
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:21,900
Okay.

153
00:12:39,733 --> 00:12:40,833
Hazel.

154
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:44,533
Why did you lie to me?

155
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:48,267
Why didn't you tell me
that Celeste was with you

156
00:12:48,367 --> 00:12:49,467
last night?

157
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:02,233
Why can't you answer me, Mikoy?

158
00:13:02,300 --> 00:13:05,433
Are you keeping a secret
from me?

159
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:08,733
Why do you have to hide
that Celeste was with you

160
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:09,900
last night?

161
00:13:11,833 --> 00:13:13,767
Did you do something?

162
00:13:17,433 --> 00:13:20,033
Nothing, we just talked.

163
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:22,400
That was it?

164
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:26,333
Why do you have to lie?

165
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:28,133
I know that you will react
that way

166
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:30,733
after the fight that happened
between the two of you.

167
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:33,300
I don't want to add anger
towards her.

168
00:13:33,367 --> 00:13:34,433
Really?

169
00:13:36,167 --> 00:13:38,167
You just talked?

170
00:13:38,233 --> 00:13:40,800
You didn't do something else?

171
00:13:40,867 --> 00:13:44,000
Yes, I promise.

172
00:13:44,067 --> 00:13:48,600
You know Mikoy, I'll admit
to you I'm not comfortable

173
00:13:48,667 --> 00:13:50,900
with Celeste being here.

174
00:13:50,967 --> 00:13:53,467
If only she'll leave Sorsogon.

175
00:13:55,767 --> 00:13:59,867
I can feel that anytime
she can steal you from me.

176
00:13:59,933 --> 00:14:01,767
You're jealous of her?

177
00:14:03,633 --> 00:14:05,733
You know that's nothing to me
and Celeste anymore.

178
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:07,700
She's getting married.

179
00:14:07,767 --> 00:14:09,867
Mikoy, just because she's
getting married

180
00:14:09,933 --> 00:14:12,400
it doesn't mean that she has no
more feelings for you.

181
00:14:12,467 --> 00:14:15,333
Sometimes you just say
there's nothing

182
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:17,233
but the truth is there's still
something going on.

183
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:22,033
You know a lot.

184
00:14:22,100 --> 00:14:23,433
There's nothing.

185
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:24,700
You should promise.

186
00:14:26,233 --> 00:14:29,500
Promise me that you have no more
feelings for Celeste.

187
00:14:31,333 --> 00:14:32,800
What's that foolishness?

188
00:14:32,867 --> 00:14:35,200
Promise me, Mikoy.

189
00:14:35,267 --> 00:14:37,833
Say that you don't love
Celeste anymore.

190
00:14:37,900 --> 00:14:40,067
And I'm the only one you love.

191
00:14:50,900 --> 00:14:52,167
Mikoy, please.

192
00:14:53,367 --> 00:14:55,233
Promise me.

193
00:14:55,300 --> 00:14:57,733
Say that you don't love
Celeste anymore.

194
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:59,967
And I'm the only one you love.

195
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:08,767
I promise that it's over
for us and Celeste.

196
00:15:08,833 --> 00:15:11,300
I have no feelings for her.

197
00:15:13,333 --> 00:15:14,367
I also promise

198
00:15:14,433 --> 00:15:16,467
that you're the only one I love.

199
00:15:16,533 --> 00:15:18,467
It's just you, okay?

200
00:15:18,533 --> 00:15:20,867
And I will be faithful to you.

201
00:15:22,367 --> 00:15:24,267
Okay?

202
00:15:24,333 --> 00:15:26,333
I promise.

203
00:15:31,867 --> 00:15:33,300
Is that okay?

204
00:15:35,867 --> 00:15:38,200
Thank you.

205
00:15:38,267 --> 00:15:39,600
Come on.

206
00:16:20,033 --> 00:16:22,800
I'm sorry too for what
I've said.

207
00:16:22,867 --> 00:16:25,133
I'll say it again,
I'm not blaming you.

208
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:32,767
We have a saying that some
people met but not destined.

209
00:16:32,833 --> 00:16:37,200
I mean we can always argue
but nothing will happen.

210
00:16:39,700 --> 00:16:41,700
Why am I thinking about that?

211
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:46,867
Do I regret it because
we are not destined?

212
00:16:46,933 --> 00:16:50,300
I have no regrets
if it's not us.

213
00:16:50,367 --> 00:16:52,433
Tonito and I look good together.

214
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:54,567
We're made for each other.

215
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:05,700
Cousin...

216
00:17:05,767 --> 00:17:07,300
hey, Cousin!

217
00:17:07,367 --> 00:17:08,367
I will fall, Cousin.

218
00:17:08,433 --> 00:17:10,067
Sorry.

219
00:17:10,133 --> 00:17:13,533
Hey! So you and Hazel have
already patched things up?

220
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:17,233
Yes.

221
00:17:17,300 --> 00:17:20,067
I already said sorry so there
will be no trouble.

222
00:17:21,733 --> 00:17:23,833
How are you and Mikoy?

223
00:17:23,900 --> 00:17:28,267
I really feel that you are
affected by Hazel's arrival.

224
00:17:28,333 --> 00:17:29,833
Am I right?

225
00:17:33,667 --> 00:17:36,900
Silence means yes.

226
00:17:36,967 --> 00:17:40,967
You know Cousin, you can say
that I'm assuming

227
00:17:41,033 --> 00:17:44,233
but could it be that destiny
is interfering

228
00:17:44,300 --> 00:17:48,300
with all that's happening now?

229
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:50,867
I'm right, isn't it?

230
00:17:53,733 --> 00:17:54,567
What is that?

231
00:17:55,833 --> 00:17:58,133
You've met but you're not
destined?

232
00:17:58,200 --> 00:18:00,167
That's cliché for me.

233
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:03,300
Wrong.

234
00:18:03,367 --> 00:18:09,600
Maybe you and Mikoy are destined
in the end. Right?

235
00:18:09,667 --> 00:18:10,933
I'm thrilled.

236
00:18:14,667 --> 00:18:18,067
You know it's you and your
absurd thoughts.

237
00:18:18,133 --> 00:18:19,300
Absorb?

238
00:18:19,367 --> 00:18:21,733
- Absurd
- Absurd ...

239
00:18:21,833 --> 00:18:23,433
here's the thing, Cousin.

240
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:26,133
You know that my tongue
has a cross.

241
00:18:27,633 --> 00:18:28,333
right?

242
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:32,033
Everything I say will happen.

243
00:18:32,100 --> 00:18:34,167
You came here to Sorsogon...

244
00:18:34,233 --> 00:18:37,333
your community service...

245
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:39,333
You've been here
for a long time.

246
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:44,600
Destiny has a plan
for you and Mikoy.

247
00:18:44,667 --> 00:18:46,300
- I love it!
- Wait,

248
00:18:46,367 --> 00:18:49,733
what you're saying
it's the greater scheme

249
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:54,200
of things that's why I stayed
longer here in Sorsogon?

250
00:18:54,267 --> 00:18:55,633
You're speaking
in English again.

251
00:18:55,733 --> 00:18:58,233
Whatever that is it Pakak .

252
00:18:58,300 --> 00:19:00,433
Means that's Pakak !

253
00:19:00,500 --> 00:19:01,933
- Pakak?
- Pakak It means...

254
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:04,800
- Frog?
- It means true and correct!

255
00:19:04,867 --> 00:19:07,300
- That's it.
- Correct?

256
00:19:07,367 --> 00:19:08,400
You're right, Cousin.

257
00:19:08,467 --> 00:19:10,067
I love it.

258
00:19:10,133 --> 00:19:11,833
I'm really thrilled.

259
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:13,467
I hope it's for all.

260
00:19:14,933 --> 00:19:18,533
I'm thrilled.

261
00:19:18,600 --> 00:19:20,467
Hey, May-May.

262
00:19:20,533 --> 00:19:24,200
- Yes.
- I brought your coconut meat

263
00:19:24,267 --> 00:19:25,833
You should go now.

264
00:19:25,900 --> 00:19:27,700
I'm sure they are already
looking for you.

265
00:19:27,767 --> 00:19:29,667
Yes, thank you, Uncle.

266
00:19:29,767 --> 00:19:32,633
Cousin, remember
what I told you.

267
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:34,100
You should go.

268
00:19:34,167 --> 00:19:35,400
Thank you.

269
00:19:39,833 --> 00:19:45,933
Celeste, don't believe too much
with your cousin May-May.

270
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:51,467
You know what she's saying
that destiny has a plan.

271
00:19:51,533 --> 00:19:53,367
There's no truth
in that, Celeste.

272
00:19:53,433 --> 00:19:57,367
The truth is you are really
from Sorsogon.

273
00:19:57,433 --> 00:20:01,433
It has nothing to do with if you
stay long here.

274
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:02,500
That's your decision.

275
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:04,800
You have the right
to stay long here.

276
00:20:04,867 --> 00:20:06,867
There's no question
with that. No problem.

277
00:20:32,033 --> 00:20:34,567
So, you spent the night
with Tonito?

278
00:20:34,633 --> 00:20:36,067
How romantic.

279
00:20:36,167 --> 00:20:37,567
Tell me all about it.

280
00:20:37,633 --> 00:20:38,933
I'm all ears.

281
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:41,633
Vivian, I know what
you're thinking.

282
00:20:41,700 --> 00:20:44,600
But nothing happened.

283
00:20:44,667 --> 00:20:48,533
I just like being with him,
you know.

284
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:51,633
I'm happy to serve him...

285
00:20:51,700 --> 00:20:54,867
Cook his favorite food.

286
00:20:54,933 --> 00:20:56,467
Oh, come on.

287
00:20:56,533 --> 00:20:59,567
You are both consenting adults.

288
00:20:59,633 --> 00:21:01,667
You used to be married to him.

289
00:21:01,733 --> 00:21:04,667
And now you're saying that
nothing happened last night?

290
00:21:06,700 --> 00:21:09,700
I just want to regain
his trust, Vivian.

291
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:11,333
That's all.

292
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:16,733
Because when I seduced him
he became aloof.

293
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:18,400
He was turned off.

294
00:21:18,467 --> 00:21:22,967
It's as if I'm sick
that he was avoiding.

295
00:21:23,033 --> 00:21:26,367
No, I don't think
that was a clever move.

296
00:21:26,433 --> 00:21:31,933
Wow, that is so virginal.

297
00:21:34,867 --> 00:21:38,000
But you have to move fast.

298
00:21:38,067 --> 00:21:39,633
Because a few months from now

299
00:21:39,700 --> 00:21:42,000
Tonito will get married
to Celeste.

300
00:21:42,100 --> 00:21:45,933
And you know we don't want
to lose.

301
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:48,500
Well, you never know.

302
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:54,433
Maybe later on it's my turn
to expose something.

303
00:22:15,167 --> 00:22:18,667
Do you even get affected
by your cousin's opinion?

304
00:22:18,733 --> 00:22:21,433
Dear, what's wrong with you?

305
00:22:21,500 --> 00:22:23,867
Will you let everything
affect you?

306
00:22:23,933 --> 00:22:24,867
I don't know, Jamaica.

307
00:22:24,933 --> 00:22:26,367
I'm just getting this weird
feeling.

308
00:22:26,433 --> 00:22:28,900
You know it's like the grand
scheme of things.

309
00:22:28,967 --> 00:22:31,533
It seems something is holding
back our marriage.

310
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:35,067
It seems like am I really
stuck here in Sorsogon forever?

311
00:22:35,133 --> 00:22:39,467
You know it's your fault why
you're there, remember?

312
00:22:39,533 --> 00:22:43,200
If you hadn't hit that replica,
you would have been here

313
00:22:43,267 --> 00:22:44,667
and you wouldn't be there.

314
00:22:44,733 --> 00:22:47,133
Did I hit it? Hello,
it's just a scratch.

315
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:48,667
I don't know but it seems like
something is delaying

316
00:22:48,767 --> 00:22:50,333
our wedding.

317
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:52,967
Dear, nothing is delaying it.

318
00:22:53,033 --> 00:22:57,333
In four months, you are getting
married here in Manila, okay?

319
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:59,767
Okay. Back to the original plan.

320
00:22:59,833 --> 00:23:02,267
Tonito and I are getting married
in less than four months.

321
00:23:02,333 --> 00:23:04,067
I'll call you back.

322
00:23:19,133 --> 00:23:20,700
Hello, love?

323
00:23:20,767 --> 00:23:23,100
Hi, Love. How are you?

324
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:25,333
You know I was thinking...

325
00:23:25,400 --> 00:23:28,233
we should get married here
in Sorsogon.

326
00:23:28,300 --> 00:23:30,200
We can get married next week.

327
00:23:30,267 --> 00:23:31,533
Huh?

328
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:33,867
We'll get married there
in Sorsogon?

329
00:23:33,933 --> 00:23:35,900
What about our wedding plans
here?

330
00:23:44,533 --> 00:23:47,733
Yeah, I'm just thinking
it's possible here.

331
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:52,367
Sorsogon is beautiful
and it's my hometown.

332
00:23:52,433 --> 00:23:53,700
Wait.

333
00:23:53,767 --> 00:23:55,500
Can you tell me
what's going on?

334
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:58,067
Why all of a sudden
you changed your mind?

335
00:23:58,133 --> 00:24:01,400
And really, you want
to get married next week?

336
00:24:01,467 --> 00:24:04,067
What happened? Why all of
a sudden, you're in a rush?

337
00:24:04,133 --> 00:24:07,033
I don't know. Maybe I'm in
a hurry.

338
00:24:07,100 --> 00:24:08,133
I just...

339
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:09,767
you know, I miss you so much.

340
00:24:09,833 --> 00:24:13,233
And I just can't wait to wake up
to you every day

341
00:24:13,300 --> 00:24:16,367
and start our lives together.

342
00:24:16,433 --> 00:24:18,633
Me too, Love. I want that.

343
00:24:18,700 --> 00:24:21,633
But we are getting married
in four months, right?

344
00:24:21,700 --> 00:24:23,233
Four months?

345
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:25,600
That's too long.

346
00:24:25,667 --> 00:24:27,533
Okay, you know...
but I'm sorry.

347
00:24:27,600 --> 00:24:29,067
I'm getting this really
weird feeling

348
00:24:29,167 --> 00:24:32,500
that it's like with everything
happening something is delaying

349
00:24:32,567 --> 00:24:33,567
our wedding.

350
00:24:33,633 --> 00:24:37,867
I feel I'm stuck
here in Sorsogon.

351
00:24:39,200 --> 00:24:41,800
Okay, calm down, Love.

352
00:24:41,867 --> 00:24:43,067
Let's discuss this later.

353
00:24:43,133 --> 00:24:45,967
I just have a virtual meeting
with a group of investors

354
00:24:46,033 --> 00:24:47,000
from Thailand.

355
00:24:47,067 --> 00:24:49,067
And then I'll call you, okay?

356
00:24:49,133 --> 00:24:50,100
Okay.

357
00:24:50,167 --> 00:24:51,300
Call me back?

358
00:24:51,367 --> 00:24:52,967
Okay, I love you.

359
00:24:53,033 --> 00:24:54,133
I love you too.

360
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:25,867
Could it be that's Celeste's
woman intuition?

361
00:25:25,933 --> 00:25:27,200
That's why she's in a hurry
for you to get married

362
00:25:27,267 --> 00:25:28,533
all of a sudden.

363
00:25:28,600 --> 00:25:31,400
Do you mean she could feel the
thing between me and Aurelia?

364
00:25:31,467 --> 00:25:32,667
Good news!

365
00:25:32,733 --> 00:25:38,167
Celeste and Tonito are getting
married here in Sorsogon.

366
00:25:38,267 --> 00:25:41,600
A partnership with Siam Global
Industry?

367
00:25:41,667 --> 00:25:43,333
And it's very timely, Aurelia.

368
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:46,667
Since you and Tonito
get along very well

369
00:25:46,733 --> 00:25:50,233
I am sending you and him
to Thailand

370
00:25:50,300 --> 00:25:52,467
to talk to our new
business partners.

371
00:25:52,533 --> 00:25:53,900
Only the two of us?

372
00:25:53,967 --> 00:25:55,400
That's it. Here it is.

373
00:25:55,467 --> 00:25:57,200
The grand talk of it all.

374
00:25:57,267 --> 00:25:58,433
Are you ready?

375
00:25:58,500 --> 00:26:02,267
The giant girlfriend of Mikoy
is willing and able

376
00:26:02,333 --> 00:26:03,500
to help me with my wedding.

377
00:26:03,567 --> 00:26:05,467
It's like she's really in a rush
for me to get married.

378
00:26:05,533 --> 00:26:07,533
I knew it. Mikoy's girlfriend
has something to do

379
00:26:07,600 --> 00:26:11,367
with the wedding that you want
to happen.

380
00:26:11,467 --> 00:26:13,233
Oh my God!

381
00:26:13,300 --> 00:26:14,833
- Are you okay?
- Are you okay?
